HEADWORD: Guimpe
<hw>Guimpe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See 2d
<er>Gimp</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of short blouse or
chemisette, worn under a low-necked dress such as a jumper or
pinafore.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a piece of starched cloth covering the shoulders of
a nun's habit.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guinea</ent>⟦br⟧
